values.comments:
This course gives students a chance to take music lessons for academic credit. It includes private study in voice, keyboard, strings, woodwind, brass, percussion, and non-western instruments. Such study is designed to meet the artistic, technical, and/or professional needs of the student.&#8232;&#8232;

Overall, students seemed very pleased with this course and the instructors. They were good resources, and students learned a lot. One wrote, “This music program is wonderful and should really be publicized more to Penn students so that more people can participate! It's fun, you learn and progress a lot, and it's a great de-stresser.”

While many students didn’t interact with Professor Ketner himself, most praised their respective instructors. Students described their teachers as “knowledgeable” and “very helpful”. &#8232;&#8232;Most of the students were very enthusiastic about the course and highly recommended it to all students.
